This is not really too relevant to the article, but that random generator makes me cringe. You can replace it with a decent quality one (xorshift) with about as many lines of code:<p><pre><code>  uint32_t genrand(uint32_t *seed)
  {
    uint32_t x = *seed;
    x ^= x << 13;
    x ^= x >> 17;
    x ^= x << 5;
    *seed = x;
    return x;
  }</code></pre>
